  }
}
</pdd-interface>
<pdd-dependency>agentic_architecture_orchestrator_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Goal
Write the `pdd/agentic_architecture.py` module.

% Role & Scope
CLI entry point for the agentic architecture workflow. Detects GitHub issue URLs, fetches issue content and comments via `gh api`, ensures repository context is available, discovers cross-project context (sibling architectures, existing .pddrc, related issues), then invokes the orchestrator. Follows the same pattern as `agentic_change.py` and `agentic_bug.py`.

% Requirements
1. Function: `run_agentic_architecture(issue_url, *, verbose=False, quiet=False, timeout_adder=0.0, use_github_state=True, skip_prompts=False, target_dir=None, force_single=False) -> Tuple[bool, str, float, str, List[str]]`
2. Return 5-tuple: (success, message, total_cost, model_used, output_files)
3. Helper: `_is_github_issue_url(url) -> bool` - Detect GitHub issue URLs
4. Helper: `_parse_github_url(url) -> Optional[Tuple[str, str, int]]` - Extract owner, repo, issue_number
5. Supported URL formats: `https://github.com/`, `https://www.github.com/`, `github.com/` followed by `{owner}/{repo}/issues/{number}`
6. Fetch issue via `gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/issues/{number}`, comments via `gh api {comments_url} --paginate`
7. Extract from issue: title, body, user.login, comments_url
8. Helper: `_ensure_repo_context(owner, repo, cwd, quiet)` - If in matching git repo, use it; if in mismatched repo, warn and use it; if not in git repo, look for `{repo}/` subdir or clone via `gh repo clone`
9. Helper: `_extract_target_dir(issue_body) -> Optional[str]` - Parse target subdirectory from issue body. Match backtick/quote-wrapped or unquoted (must contain `_` or `/`) directory names after "in". Use `target_dir` CLI param if provided, else auto-detect from issue body.
10. Cross-project context: `_parse_related_issues(body)` extracts `#NNN` refs from `### Related sub-issues:` section; `_fetch_sibling_architectures(cwd, target_dir)` scans peer directories for `architecture.json` files (skip `.`-prefixed, `node_modules`, `__pycache__`), formats as markdown table; `_read_existing_pddrc(cwd)` reads root `.pddrc` content.
11. Pass all discovered context to orchestrator: `sibling_architectures`, `existing_pddrc`, `related_issues`, `target_dir`, `force_single`

% Dependencies
<pdd.agentic_architecture_orchestrator><include>context/agentic_architecture_orchestrator_example.py</include></pdd.agentic_architecture_orchestrator>
<pdd.agentic_common><include>context/agentic_common_example.py</include></pdd.agentic_common>

% Error Handling
- Return `(False, "gh CLI not found...", 0.0, "", [])` if `gh` command not available
- Return `(False, "Invalid GitHub URL...", 0.0, "", [])` if URL parsing fails
- Return `(False, "Issue not found: {error}", 0.0, "", [])` if `gh api` fails
- Return `(False, error, 0.0, "", [])` if `_ensure_repo_context` returns an error

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/agentic_architecture.py`
